        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:50PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over West Point, or near
Lanett, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
LaGrange, West Point, Pine Mountain, Pine Mountain-Callaway Gardens,
Cannonville, Jones Crossroads, Baughs Crossroads, Smiths Crossroad,
Whitesville-Pine Lake, and Long Cane.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
